        "last_activity_date": 1507508402,
        "creation_date": 1507508402,
        "body": "<p>Due to legacy reasons, I have to use GET for my LogOutFilter and XML config. The below works.  Note I don't recommend working around the csrf protection but I've had to.<\/p>\n\n<p>This might help others.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    &lt;b:bean id=\"logoutFilter\" class=\"org.springframework.security.web.authentication.logout.LogoutFilter\"&gt;\n    &lt;b:constructor-arg name=\"logoutSuccessUrl\" value=\"/loggedOut\" /&gt;\n    &lt;b:constructor-arg name=\"handlers\"&gt;\n        &lt;b:list&gt;\n            &lt;b:bean class=\"org.springframework.security.web.authentication.logout.SecurityContextLogoutHandler\"/&gt;\n        &lt;/b:list&gt;\n    &lt;/b:constructor-arg&gt;\n    &lt;b:property name=\"logoutRequestMatcher\"&gt;\n        &lt;b:bean class=\"org.springframework.security.web.util.matcher.AntPathRequestMatcher\"&gt;\n            &lt;b:constructor-arg name=\"pattern\" value=\"/logout*\"/&gt;\n            &lt;b:constructor-arg name=\"httpMethod\" value=\"GET\"/&gt;\n        &lt;/b:bean&gt;\n    &lt;/b:property&gt;\n&lt;/b:bean&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Remember to put the custom filter in the  element<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;custom-filter before=\"CSRF_FILTER\" ref=\"logoutFilter\" /&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The key thing here is that you register your own logoutRequestMatcher<\/p>\n",
